<br>
Unsupported relative strength of Warrior vs. Knights: is there any doubt at all that a 60 Knight with simular equipment, level, and AA points can consistantly outduel a 60 Warrior?<br>
<br>
Warriors outdamaging Paladins - previous damage listings seemed to leave out IV, etc. A Warriors damage is never a big deal on any higher level mob. A Paladin's damage is sometimes quite significant.<br>
<br>
Idle Warriors during non-raid time - with the popularity of Warriors, the fact that many casters make, twink, and PL warriors, the mid-level guild growth/death cyle causing many players to retire with their melees acquired by others all have created a glut of high level Warriors. With competition for guilds, groups, drops, and the high-level equipment needed to do a Warrior's basic job - MTing, a lot of Warriors are either lfg (no 2nd account PLer to get them to 60 in 90 days), sitting in Nexus, or just not logging in except for raids.<br>
<br>
As luck would have it, I have played a Paladin and an SK recently. Both (especially the Pally) have gotten significantly more powerful in the last 6 months. Neither have any trouble at all finding groups.<br>
<br>
I'm not going to play another class, and I don't think I should have to.<br>
<br>
BB<br>
Battleblade Burlydorf<br>
60 Warrio<br>
