<br>
LvL 60 Paladin here, I would just like to state that the above statement is above all else true and very applicable in this debate.<br>
<br>
When I'm on a mid-size to high-end raid, I do not use my stuns, why?  Because it isn't my job to grab agro from the MT.  When I have somehow caught a mobs attention, I turn off attack until the MT has regained control.<br>
<br>
My role is to assist, whether it is the MT or the Cleric.  Since the upgrades that VI has implemented for the Paladins pre-Luclin, I find I am more welcome in a group sitting than not.  For that I'm enternally grateful.<br>
<br>
However, I would still much prefer to have a Warrior in that group taking the damage, so that I can do what I do best...ASSIST. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Yes, I've found myself as MT of groups.  Do I see myself equivelant to a Warrior? Heck no! Better than a warrior not by any stretch!<br>
<br>
I also have a Warrior alt. 51 now, and I would totally agree that aa skills are lacking and there should be something done to improve a Warriors TAUNT abilities.<br>
<br>
Perhaps with PoP, if not sooner...one can always hope.<br>
<br>
I just felt compelled to add my 2 cp from one paladins perspective.<br>
<br>
~Kanisah <br>
