<br>
No one here is debating the logistical benefits of being a melee class with spell casting abilities. Too many posts are showing up from Paladins and Shadowknight crying out in defense and regaling themselves to a lesser role.<br>
<br>
I don't blame you for jumping on the defensive because I know very well how badly screwed you were for years and how fragile these new improvements may seem.  After being kicked to the ground for 2+ years, you are justified to feel paniced about discussions like these.<br>
<br>
However, the fact is that warriors have been slowly and quietly neglected for awhile now and it is logical to point to where other improvements have been made and how it affects the main melee class that has been overlooked for 2 yrs.<br>
<br>
Oh and as for the &quot;gimp healer, I want to tank&quot; statement. Boo hoo, you should have made a warrior. People who pick a class to play and then constantly want to be another class should just play that other class. This isn't a sex change clinic waiting room. You can't turn your paladin into a warrior by wishing it or stealing aggro.<br>
