Is it a flaw in the Game, perhaps yes. Ye Auld Taunt Button; when hit; <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> should</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> create &quot;X&quot; amount of aggro; which should for all intents and purposes; be at least equal if not a slight bit more than comparable to a Pal/SK spell.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong; Pal/SK spells are <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> great</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> for steering/placing MoB's; keeping the robewearers and priests alive ( don't want the person being hit; a pal/sk can pull a mob off someone faster than i can type &quot;assist me on %t ! &quot;; pulling; and to increase DPS. But to have those same spells be so overpowering that the Warrior's Taunt Button ( in comparison our <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> ONLY</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> character based means of generating Added Aggro ) is only as good as what weapons and +taunt/hate weapons we wield is bullsh*t. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=172088">Shikarii T'Zaii</A> - <A HREF="http://www.divinelegend.com">Divine Legend</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugremli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gremli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/10/02 11:26:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=150>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: The State of Warriors in EQ</span><hr size=1> I think most of the salient points about warriors demise have already been made, particularly concerning damage mitigation and taunt.  <br>
<br>
Several people have chimed in about paladins and particularly SK's lamenting the fact that they are not wanted in groups... so they are forced to solo.  What strikes me is that even if this was true...people think this is a failing on their class, when in fact its what they signed up for.  As a warrior when I am not wanted in a group, I really have no other option but to sit there and wait.  I can't easily solo anything, and certainly not efficiently (im excluding the mega equipped and speaking to 99 percent of the remaining warrior population lvls 30-58 )  .<br>
<br>
Warriors were supposed to require less exp to level than hybrids to make up for the fact that there was alot of downtime to playing a warrior.  Not just downtime in the sense of soloing and waiting to regen health, but downtime in the sense that warriors needed to have a group to be effective.  <br>
<br>
Removing the hybrid exp penalty allowed hybrids to level far quicker than warriors.  Making hybrids better tanks makes it that much harder for a warrior to find a group.  So I would say there definitely is a complaint for the warrior community. What else do we bring to the table if it isnt tanking?  (throw that stupid player skill argument out the window, assume equally skilled players)  <br>
<br>
When we can't find a group after two hours, we don't have the option of soloing.  there may be a location halfway accross norath where a warrior could solo at any given point in his career (very poorly), but the main point of the argument is that we all agree hybrids do it much better, and just about anywhere.  <br>
<br>
I think the most convincing argument that has been made, and that could be placed to verant is that warriors are a pure melee class that focus on defensive disciplines.  Monks are a pure melee class that focus on offensive disciplines.  Monks are on their own offensive table, but warriors share the defensive table.  There really should be a warrior only defensive table.  It is the only thing that sets a warrior apart, since it certainly is not gear.<br>
<br>
As far as taunt is concerned, I consider taunt the ability of the warrior to place himself between the mob and his target.  I don't consider it to be some magic button that makes a mob turn around and attack you instead.  Unfortunately game mechanics make it look like that, but it represents a tanks skill to force a mob to go through him to get to the rest of the group.  I guess in a game where mobs can go through walls the whole notion is kind of silly.  Warriors should be able to place themselves between the guy with the club and the guy with the spellbook.   <br>
<br>
I would be happy if warriors were moved to their own defensive table.  If this is not going to be a solution that verant entertains, then dissolve the notion of a pure warrior, and give &quot;hybrid&quot; skills to all warriors so that current &quot;pure&quot; warriors become another hybrid class with unique abilities.  It's not what i signed up for, but its more fair than what we currently have.<br>
<br>
-gremli<br>
<br>
