<br>
I would love to be able to solo better. It's just fun, ya know? Being at the high end game with high end weapons and high end gear, after plugging away for however long as a lowbie, it's fun to walk up to a scound in Echo and tear it a new a-hole, all the while watching my sod, primal and elphorn's procing up a storm. But then I have to sit and wait for 10 minutes to heal. It makes it so that my fun level is irrelevant, cause if I want to get my AA points up, I need to be efficient. So I can't solo, even though that's what I enjoy the most.<br>
<br>
I would love it if taunt actually worked. I know it works, but we all know the reliability of it. I have no problems taking aggro and holding aggro cause any pally or sk or whoever I see with the wrong weapons (like stun procing ones) or casting the wrong spells gets a reaming in /shout. But still, even when everyone has their attack off and takes a step back and the MT is taunting his butt off, sometimes they still can't get aggro. At the very least there should be a simple way to switch MTs on a AoW type mob without risking half your damage output. And it shouldn't be a really complicated and hard thing to do. <br>
<br>
I would love it if our AA skills did what they were supposed to. Can ANYONE at VI justify physical enhancement for everyone but the one class that truly NEEDS it? How utterly stupid was the person who decided which classes get what AAs? And whats the deal with BW being a class defining ability? Are you completely insane?<br>
<br>
But the bottom line is this: I'm a warrior. I exist in this game for 2 reasons; to die and to make sure I'm the only one who dies. Some of my fondest memories playing EQ are of me stoically facing down a train of mobs as my group runs for the exit. I relegated myself to that position long ago, as I think have most warriors. It's the nature of our class to take it in the pie hole. That's probably why warriors are always so quiet about class balance stuff. As long as we can stand there and make the mob hit us and take the beating (within reason) we're a happy group. <br>
<br>
But now we don't even have that.<br>
<br>
It just really bothers me that what should be the flagship class of the melee genre is fast being relegated to encounter specific roles. We are no longer indispensable. This needs to change. <p>Shelrabbi Hassida<BR>
