<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usmiledmonk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smile d monk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/10/02 2:25:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=159>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://labtech.home.texas.net/smile_ez.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  The State of Warriors in EQ (from the viewpoint of a monk)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> With monks getting high AC/HP stuff, warriors (and paladins/sks) need to catch up to the monks in mitigation<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I’m dieing here…no laughing…really. The top end best of the best AC items a monk can get are horribly rare and tough to get…which isn’t as much of an issue as the fact the next step down from the top end (for example) tunic is roughly half the ac. There isn’t an in between with monk equipment really. You have “HOLY CRAP, this is AWESOME” and “I could probably do more damage with a toilet brush…you got a dish rag I can borrow? It’s got more ac than this planer armor/velous quest armor I’ve got”. <br>
<br>
There’s really little middle of the road as far as equipment for monks goes. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> What the hell is up with a monk getting a pair of leggings that have 60AC?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The AOW is no pushover and to get him you’ll likely have several monks there to do him…he’s on a long spawn timer…his pants are a rare drop (EXTREMELY rare from what I hear). The next best pants for a monk are I believe closer to 25 ac. Quite a difference there. <br>
<br>
I will say though, with very good (not the “WOW, can I worship at your feet for awhile?” stuff) armor a monk can get to 1200-1300 ac. <br>
<br>
I like the idea of pulling the ac cap and giving warriors the full benefit of the armor they get…an equivalently equipped warrior would likely have closer to 1700 to 1800 ac. With no cap that would be a significant difference.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Other classes need to look at warriors and ask themselves, &quot;What would I do if my class defining ability was taken away?&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This in reference to damage mitigation and taunt.<br>
<br>
I’ve played a monk since dec 15 1999…I’m 60th level and I don’t think I’ve ever had an issue getting agro from a warrior, no matter how much they mash that taunt key. Even a warrior 2 or 3 levels above me (when I was younger) was this an issue. I can stand back at max melee range, using a 2h weapon to hit less often, and STILL get agro occasionally from an entire raid full of warriors. I have even stolen the kill a time or two on a raid when I fell through the cracks while groups were made (got in a group pretty fast after that though *snicker*)<br>
<br>
My point is Warriors have ALWAYS had problems with taunt working to keep agro from me when I’m actually DOING my max DPS (thus making doing more damage than a warrior less than worthless…what’s the point of dealing more damage if I get my face pulled off and made into a lampshade?). It sucked then, and it still sucks. <br>
<br>
Even with all the equipment I have that puts me as close to a tank as I’ve ever been, I still splode if I get a nasty mob’s attention for too long. <br>
<br>
If nothing else, for the monks (would put “For the children”, but figured that’s going a bit far), I truly hope warriors DO get a taunt that is finally worth a crap…and the ability to stand there and suck it up they way they were meant to. That’s supposed to be their job. My job is to get them to the warriors, (and buy one for the team if I bring too many friends) the warriors job has always been to keep it’s attention so everybody and carve their initials on it’s right cheek. <br>
 <p>Smile
<br>Monk 60th belt
<br><b><i>"Te audire no possum. Musa sapientum fixa est in aure"</b><i>
<br>I can't hear you. I have a banana in my ear.
